ðŸŽ PROTOCOL-ORIENTED PROGRAMMING â€” THE ULTIMATE CHEATSHEET
âœ… 1. What is a Protocol?
A blueprint of methods, properties, and requirements.
protocol Movable {
    var speed: Int { get }
    func move()
}
âœ… 2. Protocol Conformance
struct Car: Movable {
    let speed = 100
    func move() { print("Car moving at \(speed)") }
}
âœ… 3. Protocol Extensions (POPâ€™s Superpower)
Give default implementations to protocols.
extension Movable {
    func move() {
        print("Moving at \(speed)")
    }
}
Any conforming type gets this for free.
âœ… 4. POP vs OOP (Why POP is better in Swift)
OOP (Class Inheritance)	POP (Protocols)
Single inheritance only	Mix unlimited protocols
Heavy & opinionated	Lightweight & flexible
Base class bloat	Small modular pieces
Runtime dispatch	Compile-time safe
Mutates state	Encourages immutability
Apple engineers prefer POP for frameworks like SwiftUI, Combine, and Foundation.
âœ… 5. Protocol Composition
Combine multiple protocols:
protocol Runnable { func run() }
protocol Jumpable { func jump() }

func train(athlete: Runnable & Jumpable) {
    athlete.run()
    athlete.jump()
}
âœ… 6. Associated Types (Advanced POP)
Used when a protocol needs a generic placeholder.
protocol DataSource {
    associatedtype Item
    func getItems() -> [Item]
}
Then implement:
struct IntSource: DataSource {
    func getItems() -> [Int] { [1,2,3] }
}
âœ… 7. Protocols + Generics = GOD MODE
func printItems<T: DataSource>(_ source: T) {
    print(source.getItems())
}
Works for ANY type matching the protocol âœ”
âœ… 8. Self Requirements
Ensures functions return the same type.
protocol Duplicateable {
    func duplicate() -> Self
}
Used by SwiftUI a LOT.
âœ… 9. Mutating Requirements
Needed for value types (structs):
protocol Counter {
    mutating func increment()
}
âœ… 10. Static Requirements
Protocols can demand static members:
protocol Identifiable {
    static var idPrefix: String { get }
}
âœ… 11. POP Real-World Example (Apple Style)
Reusable Networking Layer
protocol Requestable {
    associatedtype Model: Decodable
    var url: URL { get }
}

extension Requestable {
    func fetch() async throws -> Model {
        let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared.data(from: url)
        return try JSONDecoder().decode(Model.self, from: data)
    }
}
Then every API call = 5 lines ðŸš€
struct UserRequest: Requestable {
    typealias Model = User
    let url = URL(string: "https://api.github.com/users")!
}
âœ… 12. POP in SwiftUI & Combine (Important)
SwiftUI views rely on protocols, not classes.
Examples:
View, Identifiable, ObservableObject, Publisher
Everything POP.
